### Key gap (Finding 1 — MEDIUM, score 6/10)
**The 4 updated visual screenshots never show the new pills.** Both visual tests (`chat-panel-empty` and `chat-panel-with-messages`) use mock data without `applied_changes.context_things`, so `activeContextThings` is always empty and the new `hidden md:flex` block is never entered. If the pills broke tomorrow, all 4 screenshots would still pass.

**Fix**: Add two new Playwright tests (`chat-panel-with-context-pills-desktop` and dark variant) that inject mock messages with `context_things`. Full example code in the artifact.

### Secondary gap (Finding 2 — LOW, score 3/10)
The existing unit test at line 171 renders the desktop pill buttons but never asserts on them or clicks them. The `openThingDetailStore` click handler is untested at unit level. Simple to fix: one new `it` block in `ChatPanel.test.tsx` + add `thingTypes: []` to `mockStore`.
